186
00:07:43,041 --> 00:07:44,458
--Yeah, me too.
--No, me first.

187
00:07:44,541 --> 00:07:46,375
[REITA] All right, ladies.
Who else wants to talk to me?

188
00:07:46,458 --> 00:07:47,458
[BOY] Hey, what about us?

189
00:07:47,541 --> 00:07:49,041
Uh, let's see now.

190
00:07:49,125 --> 00:07:51,083
Old dude, old hag, old hag,
really old hag.

191
00:07:51,166 --> 00:07:52,291
Now yours is a--

192
00:07:52,375 --> 00:07:53,666
[STUDENT]
At least pretend to care.

193
00:07:53,750 --> 00:07:55,500
Have him check yours, Hairo.

194
00:07:55,583 --> 00:07:57,125
No, I don't have to.

195
00:07:57,208 --> 00:07:59,833
Aw, man. Your guardian
spirit's incredible.

196
00:07:59,916 --> 00:08:01,083
He's an intensely
passionate man.

197
00:08:01,166 --> 00:08:02,833
Plays tennis.

198
00:08:02,916 --> 00:08:05,958
He's got boundless energy.
I think maybe his name's Shu--

199
00:08:06,041 --> 00:08:07,208
He's not dead yet.

200
00:08:07,291 --> 00:08:09,208
Guardian spirits? Sounds dumb.

201
00:08:09,291 --> 00:08:11,541
Still, suppose it'd be rude
not to hear you out,

202
00:08:11,625 --> 00:08:13,875
so tell me about mine
or whatever. Don't care.

203
00:08:13,958 --> 00:08:15,291
[SAIKI]
He totally cares.

204
00:08:15,375 --> 00:08:17,625
Your guardian spirit--
Oh, wow, it's kind of abnormal.

205
00:08:17,708 --> 00:08:19,625
Huh? What does that mean?

206
00:08:19,708 --> 00:08:22,291
Is it some kind of demon
or monster or dark spirit?

207
00:08:22,375 --> 00:08:23,875
So what is it,
not that I care--

208
00:08:23,958 --> 00:08:26,250
--A Chihuahua.
--A Chihuahua?

209
00:08:26,333 --> 00:08:27,833
[GIRL]
A Chihuahua, he said.

210
00:08:27,916 --> 00:08:30,125
How dare he insult me like that.
This guy's a fraud.

211
00:08:30,208 --> 00:08:31,833
Hey, now. What's goin'
on here, a festival?

212
00:08:31,916 --> 00:08:33,583
[SAIKI]
Now here's someone abnormal.

213
00:08:33,666 --> 00:08:35,916
New kid says he can see
guardian spirits, but he lies.

214
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:37,458
Oh, cool. What's that?

215
00:08:37,541 --> 00:08:39,000
Now no pushing.
Everyone just wait your turn.

216
00:08:39,083 --> 00:08:41,166
Hey, what's my guardian spirit?

217
00:08:41,250 --> 00:08:44,541
Nendou's guardian?
Now that I am curious about.

218
00:08:44,625 --> 00:08:46,625
Okay, let's see.
Yours is a politician.

219
00:08:46,708 --> 00:08:47,916
What? Really?
Aw, denied.

220
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,875
[bell chimes]

221
00:08:49,958 --> 00:08:51,583
Got to say. I'm really happy
I transferred to this school.

222
00:08:51,666 --> 00:08:54,333
I can already tell I'm gonna
have an awesome time here.

223
00:08:54,416 --> 00:08:57,125
Say, wanna hear about
your guardian spirit, Saiki?

224
00:08:57,208 --> 00:08:59,666
Me? I couldn't care less,
but tell what him his

225
00:08:59,750 --> 00:09:01,000
'cause he's getting
really annoying.

226
00:09:01,083 --> 00:09:02,708
Aw, just shut up.

227
00:09:02,791 --> 00:09:04,625
I've told you not to follow me
everywhere. I hate you.

228
00:09:04,708 --> 00:09:06,125
[SAIKI]
Whoa. What got into you?

229
00:09:06,208 --> 00:09:08,083
Ow.

230
00:09:08,166 --> 00:09:09,166
[gasps]

231
00:09:11,041 --> 00:09:12,833
[groans]

232
00:09:12,916 --> 00:09:14,375
[REITA] What?
You're not a ghost?

233
00:09:14,458 --> 00:09:15,875
[SAIKI]
You really didn't know?

234
00:09:15,958 --> 00:09:17,333
But all this time
he's been following us,

235
00:09:17,416 --> 00:09:19,166
you never once
acknowledged his presence.

236
00:09:19,250 --> 00:09:20,666
I thought you
couldn't see him.

237
00:09:20,750 --> 00:09:21,750
[SAIKI]
I just ignore him.

238
00:09:21,833 --> 00:09:23,375
--What was that all about?
--No way.

239
00:09:23,458 --> 00:09:25,250
It's true. I see
an old hag behind him.

240
00:09:25,333 --> 00:09:27,875
He can't tell the difference
between the living and the dead.

241
00:09:27,958 --> 00:09:29,791
