sure have it rough.

242
00:09:29,875 --> 00:09:31,666
[REITA] Hey, Saiki, there's
something I've got to show you,

243
00:09:31,750 --> 00:09:34,166
but you'll have to touch me
using your psychometry power.

244
00:09:34,250 --> 00:09:36,125
I think when you see this,

245
00:09:36,208 --> 00:09:38,291
you'll understand why
I was so confused before.

246
00:09:38,375 --> 00:09:39,583
Is that--?

247
00:09:39,666 --> 00:09:41,166
[snores]

248
00:09:41,250 --> 00:09:43,250
Allow me to introduce
my guardian spirit.

249
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:45,250
[SAIKI] I'm sorry.
You really do have it rough.

250
00:09:45,333 --> 00:09:48,041
Wow.

251
00:09:48,125 --> 00:09:50,416
[man singing in Japanese]

252
00:09:52,041 --> 00:09:55,333
♪

253
00:09:57,041 --> 00:10:01,583
Uhh, I can't.
It's too heavy. Aah.

254
00:10:01,666 --> 00:10:05,125
Whoa. You okay? This is heavy.
Where are you takin' it?

255
00:10:05,208 --> 00:10:06,916
The teachers' lounge.

256
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:09,291
Kineshi Hairo--our class rep
and pillar of the community.

257
00:10:09,375 --> 00:10:11,500
Due to his kindness
and strong leadership,

258
00:10:11,583 --> 00:10:13,541
everybody looks up to him.
Although...

259
00:10:13,625 --> 00:10:15,791
But... first I want you
to bring it this far.

260
00:10:15,875 --> 00:10:18,791
We can only get stronger
by pushing past our own limits.

261
00:10:18,875 --> 00:10:21,416
Come on. Great job.
Don't give up.

262
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:23,125
Keep going. You can do it.

263
00:10:23,208 --> 00:10:24,500
[SAIKI] He's so positive,

264
00:10:24,583 --> 00:10:26,375
it falls more on
the side of obnoxious.

265
00:10:26,458 --> 00:10:29,083
Good hustle. Now it's time
to push myself.

266
00:10:29,166 --> 00:10:30,833
I'm gonna carry it
the rest of the way

267
00:10:30,916 --> 00:10:32,083
while doing bunny hops.
What?

268
00:10:32,166 --> 00:10:33,833
Still, as tough
as he is on others,

269
00:10:33,916 --> 00:10:35,750
he's even tougher on himself.

270
00:10:35,833 --> 00:10:38,541
That's probably what inspires my
classmates to follow his lead.

271
00:10:38,625 --> 00:10:40,291
Ooh, we should
hop along with him.

272
00:10:40,375 --> 00:10:42,291
We don't have stuff to carry,
but we could pretend.

273
00:10:42,375 --> 00:10:45,791
Aah. I'm coming for you,
teachers' lounge.

274
00:10:45,875 --> 00:10:47,666
[SAIKI]
I don't hate him as a person,

275
00:10:47,750 --> 00:10:49,375
but the two of us
probably wouldn't mix very well.

276
00:10:49,458 --> 00:10:50,875
[bell chimes]

277
00:10:50,958 --> 00:10:52,791
Hey, Saiki, did you know
that scientists say

278
00:10:52,875 --> 00:10:54,666
the average person sweats
about 300 milliliters

279
00:10:54,750 --> 00:10:56,250
every night
while they're sleeping?

280
00:10:56,333 --> 00:10:57,750
You're telling me why?

281
00:10:57,833 --> 00:10:59,458
Well, the school's
Sports Day is coming up,

282
00:10:59,541 --> 00:11:01,375
and I'm working on building
the entry gate for it now.

283
00:11:01,458 --> 00:11:03,083
Kudo was supposed to help me,

284
00:11:03,166 --> 00:11:04,583
but then he went
and came down with a cold.

285
00:11:04,666 --> 00:11:06,125
You can't quit on me now.

286
00:11:06,208 --> 00:11:08,166
Beating a cold
is just a matter of willpower.

287
00:11:08,250 --> 00:11:09,833
You show that stupid virus
who's boss. Never give up.

288
00:11:09,916 --> 00:11:11,250
[SAIKI] Are you a monster?

289
00:11:11,333 --> 00:11:12,708
[HAIRO] Really,
it's almost done.

290
00:11:12,791 --> 00:11:14,750
All we have to do is connect
the arch to the pedestals.

291
00:11:14,833 --> 00:11:16,750
So if you just give me a han--

292
00:11:16,833 --> 00:11:19,125
[screams]

293
00:11:19,208 --> 00:11:21,958
Pedestal? You were standing
just fine yesterday.

294
00:11:22,041 --> 00:11:23,708
Hey, come on, get up, pedestal.

295
00:11:23,791 --> 00:11:25,583
[SAIKI] Pep talks
don't work on pedestals.

296
00:11:25,666 --> 00:11:28,583
What a pain. This is more than
we can fix ourselves,

297
00:11:28,666 --> 00:11:30,083
--so I'm gonna go now.
--Hold it there, Saiki.

298
00:11:30,166 --> 00:11:31,750
We can do this.
If we work fast,

299
00:11:31,833 --> 00:11:33,875
we'll finish before
the last train leaves.

300
00:11:33,958 --> 00:11:35,791
Gimme a break.

301
00:11:35,875 --> 00:11:38,000
Waah. You can do it.
I believe in you.

302
00:11:38,083 --> 00:11:40,000
Don't give up.
Give it all you've got.

303
00:11:40,083 --> 00:11:42,541
Please stop. What a pain.
Why am I even here?

304
00:11:42,625 --> 00:11:44,083
[HAIRO] Never give up.

305
00:11:44,166 --> 00:11:46,291
Hard to figure out
how much strength to use.

306
00:11:46,375 --> 00:11:48,916
Damn it. This is a catastrophe.
We ran out of lumber.

307
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:51,000
[SAIKI] So we should
give up? Give up already.

308
00:11:51,083 --> 00:11:53,166
Saiki, keep it up.
I'm counting on you.

309
00:11:53,250 --> 00:11:54,333
Waah.

310
00:11:54,416 --> 00:11:56,708
Seriously? I could just go home,

311
00:11:56,791 --> 00:11:59,333
but then I'll have to deal with
a guilt trip from him tomorrow.

312
00:11:59,416 --> 00:12:01,125
How could you just abandon me?

313
00:12:01,208 --> 00:12:02,833
What part of "never give up"
don't you understand?

314
00:12:02,916 --> 00:12:05,041
[SAIKI] It'll be a lot easier
if I work without tools,

315
00:12:05,125 --> 00:12:08,041
seeing as I'm not used to them.

316
00:12:08,125 --> 00:12:10,708
But it'll look suspicious
if I finish too much.

317
00:12:10,791 --> 00:12:12,208
[hisses]

318
00:12:12,291 --> 00:12:14,791
Might as well read a book
while I wait.

319
00:12:17,083 --> 00:12:19,458
It's taking a long time.
What's he doing?

320
00:12:19,541 --> 00:12:22,666
Is he slacking off?
No, that's not like him.

321
00:12:22,750 --> 00:12:25,916
Guess I should try to find him.
Clairvoyance.

322
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:29,708
Ah, there he is.
What's he doing? Uhh.

323
00:12:29,791 --> 00:12:31,708
[groans]

324
00:12:31,791 --> 00:12:33,916
[SAIKI] Where the hell
did he get that?

325
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,916
The lumber shop
may have been closed,

326
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:38,083
but there are always logs
on the ground.

327
00:12:38,166 --> 00:12:39,625
[GIRL] What's wrong with him?

328
00:12:39,708 --> 00:12:41,583
Did somebody tie him
to a tree or something?

329
00:12:41,666 --> 00:12:43,791
I will never, ever give up.

330
00:12:43,875 --> 00:12:47,125
You know, sometimes it really is
better to just give up.

331
00:12:47,208 --> 00:12:49,791
Saiki's working hard right now,
all by himself.

332
00:12:49,875 --> 00:12:52,083
I can't give up.
I have to do this for him.

333
00:12:52,166 --> 00:12:53,458
I'm fine. Please give up.

334
00:12:53,541 --> 00:12:55,541
Uh. What the hell?
What now?

335
00:12:55,625 --> 00:12:57,916
[HAIRO] The log. There's--
It's covered in fungi.

336
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:59,083
Then just ditch it.

337
00:12:59,166 --> 00:13:01,041
[HAIRO] No, I can't give up now.

338
00:13:01,125 --> 00:13:02,750
[Hairo screaming]

339
00:13:06,333 --> 00:13:07,958
That's some slimy fungus.

340
00:13:08,041 --> 00:13:10,208
Sorry I took so long,
but don't worry.

341
00:13:10,291 --> 00:13:11,750
We can still finish by morning.

342
00:13:11,833 --> 00:13:13,416
[BOY] Oh, you'll finish
sooner than that.

343
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:15,083
[HAIRO]
What're you guys doin' here?

344
00:13:15,166 --> 00:13:16,666
We were doing
after-school activities

345
00:13:16,750 --> 00:13:18,291
and saw you sliding by
on an out-of-control log.

346
00:13:18,375 --> 00:13:20,166
[GIRL] Since you
always help us out...

347
00:13:20,250 --> 00:13:21,583
[BOY] We wanted to help you.

348
00:13:21,666 --> 00:13:24,916
Wow. 'Kay, let's do it.
Huddle up, guys.

349
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,750
--Let's go, team.
--Can we get started now?

350
00:13:26,833 --> 00:13:28,583
Stop the fungi from breeding.

351
00:13:28,666 --> 00:13:29,875
Saw like crazy.

352
00:13:29,958 --> 00:13:31,041
Hey. No slacking off.

353
00:13:31,125 --> 00:13:33,208
[strains]

354
00:13:33,291 --> 00:13:34,833
[BOY]
We're finished. It's done.

355
00:13:34,916 --> 00:13:36,250
[SECOND BOY]
Oh, it looks pretty good.

356
00:13:36,333 --> 00:13:37,625
[SAIKI]
What a pain.

357
00:13:37,708 --> 00:13:39,500
I didn't think
it'd take this long.

358
00:13:39,583 --> 00:13:41,416
Normal people
have it rough, too.

359
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:43,500
Though doing this kind of thing
isn't so bad once in a while.

360
00:13:43,583 --> 00:13:45,125
Hey, but wait.

361
00:13:45,208 --> 00:13:46,750
Why are we preparing stuff
for the Sports Day now?

362
00:13:46,833 --> 00:13:48,791
It's still
a month away, right?

363
00:13:48,875 --> 00:13:53,500
Are you kidding?
A month will pass in no time.

364
00:13:53,583 --> 00:13:56,958
[SAIKI]
Yeah. We don't mix at all.

365
00:13:57,041 --> 00:13:59,500
♪

366
00:14:02,041 --> 00:14:04,916
[WOMAN] We're leaving, Kuu.
Hold down the fort, okay?

367
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,541
We'll be back around nightfall.

368
00:14:06,625 --> 00:14:09,333
They're going to a wedding.
Someone from Dad's work.

369
00:14:09,416 --> 00:14:11,416
I don't understand why Kirishima
is having his wedding

370
00:14:11,500 --> 00:14:14,041
smack in the middle of summer.
This heat is unbearable.

371
00:14:14,125 --> 00:14:15,458
I mean, honey, don't you agree?

372
00:14:15,541 --> 00:14:17,375
It's even hotter outside.

373
00:14:17,458 --> 00:14:19,416
[SAIKI] You guys are hot because
you're clinging to each other.

374
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:21,833
Anyway, Kusuo, are you sure
you don't wanna come with us?

375
00:14:21,916 --> 00:14:23,541
You've met Kirishima before,
right?

376
00:14:23,625 --> 00:14:25,458
Not interested.

377
00:14:25,541 --> 00:14:28,458
On the surface, it seems like
a happy occasion full of joy.

378
00:14:28,541 --> 00:14:30,791
But underneath...
Welcome to my misery.

379
00:14:30,875 --> 00:14:33,333
It's a hotbed of schadenfreude,
pity, and jealousy.

380
00:14:33,416 --> 00:14:34,583
You know, a wedding.

381
00:14:34,666 --> 00:14:36,041
Uch, marrying her? Poor guy.

382
00:14:36,125 --> 00:14:37,916
I'm not in the mood
for any of that.

383
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:40,041
Aw, well, that's too bad.
You know, your psychic powers

384
00:14:40,125 --> 00:14:41,333
would've livened up
the reception.

385
00:14:41,416 --> 00:14:42,666
Those things are stuffy.

386
00:14:42,750 --> 00:14:44,541
My powers
aren't for your amusement.

387
00:14:44,625 --> 00:14:47,750
Finally, it's quiet.
Maybe I'll watch some TV.

388
00:14:47,833 --> 00:14:50,666
Hmm, this place is a mess.

389
00:14:50,750 --> 00:14:53,666
Well, I guess I could help with
the cleaning now and then.

390
00:14:55,041 --> 00:14:57,000
♪

391
00:14:59,125 --> 00:15:02,041
There's so much dust
under the furniture.

392
00:15:02,125 --> 00:15:03,833
Seriously, how could anyone

393
00:15:03,916 --> 00:15:05,541
have let it get
this dirty in here?

394
00:15:05,625 --> 00:15:09,333
I mean, really, it's a wonder
we don't have bug--Unh.

395
00:15:13,166 --> 00:15:14,583
[screes]

396
00:15:14,666 --> 00:15:16,208
[SAIKI]
There was a cockroach.

397
00:15:16,291 --> 00:15:18,250
For the most part,
I'm unshakeable,

398
00:15:18,333 --> 00:15:20,750
but there's one thing
I can't stand--bugs.

399
00:15:20,833 --> 00:15:23,458
And it's not because
they're gross or anything.

400
00:15:23,541 --> 00:15:25,333
Okay, well, maybe a little.

401
00:15:25,416 --> 00:15:27,666
But the real reason I hate bugs
is I can't predict their moves.

402
00:15:27,750 --> 00:15:30,208
When it comes to telepathy,
I can communicate with

403
00:15:30,291 --> 00:15:32,750
most of the animal kingdom,
not just humans.

404
00:15:32,833 --> 00:15:35,708
But bugs are so small that
I can't read their thoughts.

405
00:15:35,791 --> 00:15:39,208
Just can't get inside their
tiny little bug brains.

406
00:15:39,291 --> 00:15:41,000
And sure,
if I used psychokinesis,

407
00:15:41,083 --> 00:15:42,333
I could catch 'em easily,

408
00:15:42,416 --> 00:15:44,208
but I don't even want
my psychokinesis

409
00:15:44,291 --> 00:15:45,750
to touch those icky critters.

410
00:15:45,833 --> 00:15:47,500
Okay, so teleporting to Texas

411
00:15:47,583 --> 00:15:49,416
may have been
a bit of an overreaction,

412
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:51,125
but as long as there's
a roach in that house--

413
00:15:51,208 --> 00:15:54,041
Zuzuya's delivering some
Yukimi Garlic Chives Daifuku.

414
00:15:54,125 --> 00:15:55,625
Be sure to answer the door.

415
00:15:55,708 --> 00:15:58,083
That's right.
Mom's expecting a package,

416
00:15:58,166 --> 00:15:59,583
and I've already been gone
five minutes.

417
00:15:59,666 --> 00:16:02,458
I have no choice.
Got to go home.

418
00:16:02,541 --> 00:16:05,416
The roach was downstairs,
so I should be safe up here.

419
00:16:05,500 --> 00:16:07,833
What do I do
when the delivery guy shows up?

420
00:16:07,916 --> 00:16:10,208
I'll have to go down there.
I wish Dad was home.

421
00:16:10,291 --> 00:16:11,958
Aah, it's a roach.

422
00:16:12,041 --> 00:16:13,750
[SAIKI] Right. Dad's useless
when it comes to bugs.

423
00:16:13,833 --> 00:16:15,375
What's that? There's a roach?

424
00:16:15,458 --> 00:16:16,958
[SAIKI] Mom, on the other hand,
would scoop it up

425
00:16:17,041 --> 00:16:18,708
like an ace infielder
catching a ground ball

426
00:16:18,791 --> 00:16:20,916
--and toss it outside.
--You're out of here.

427
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:23,291
Maybe I should bring her home
using teleportation.

428
00:16:23,375 --> 00:16:25,166
--[doorbell rings]
--He's here.

429
00:16:25,250 --> 00:16:28,250
Why'd he have to come now?
No, wait. This is actually good.

430
00:16:28,333 --> 00:16:31,000
Once I get the package, there's
no need for me to be home.

431
00:16:31,083 --> 00:16:33,250
Soon as they leave,
I can teleport far, far away.

432
00:16:33,333 --> 00:16:36,625
Only question is,
how to get to the door?

433
00:16:36,708 --> 00:16:38,541
Oh, yeah, nailed it.

434
00:16:38,625 --> 00:16:40,375
[cicadas humming]

435
00:16:42,958 --> 00:16:44,166
[hisses]

436
00:16:44,250 --> 00:16:47,125
Russia
St. Petersburg

437
00:16:47,208 --> 00:16:49,458
There was a Nendou.

438
00:16:49,541 --> 00:16:52,125
Okay, maybe
I overreacted again.

439
00:16:52,208 --> 00:16:54,416
But first a cockroach shows up,
then Nendou.

440
00:16:54,500 --> 00:16:57,583
Two small-brained creatures
whose actions I can't predict.

441
00:16:57,666 --> 00:16:59,333
Can you blame me
for freaking out?

442
00:16:59,416 --> 00:17:01,166
I just can't seem
to catch a-- Of course.

443
00:17:01,250 --> 00:17:02,750
Why didn't I think of that?

444
00:17:02,833 --> 00:17:04,125
Granted, I only saw him
for a second,

445
00:17:04,208 --> 00:17:05,708
but he had some kind of a net.

446
00:17:05,791 --> 00:17:07,458
Ah, no problem.
Leave it to me, pal.

447
00:17:07,541 --> 00:17:09,416
Doesn't matter
if it's one roach or a hundred,

448
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:11,125
--I'll get rid of 'em all.
--Great.

449
00:17:11,208 --> 00:17:13,458
Well, I'll be in Brazil,
so let me know when you're done.

450
00:17:13,541 --> 00:17:15,666
There they are.
There's two of 'em under there.

451
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:17,625
That's even worse.

452
00:17:17,708 --> 00:17:20,958
Can I lift this thing?
Huh. Lot lighter than it looks.

453
00:17:21,041 --> 00:17:23,541
If it helps get rid of those
monsters, I'll lend a hand.

454
00:17:23,625 --> 00:17:25,833
Ah, now there's
nowhere to run.

455
00:17:25,916 --> 00:17:28,458
You're not supposed to let go.
Anyway, take 'em outside--

456
00:17:28,541 --> 00:17:29,833
[splatters]

457
00:17:29,916 --> 00:17:31,375
[NENDOU] Hey,
you got any tissues?

458
00:17:31,458 --> 00:17:34,583
Well, do you want to
go get some ramen?

459
00:17:34,666 --> 00:17:37,208
I hate to say this
after all your help,

460
00:17:37,291 --> 00:17:39,541
but could you, leave, like, now?

461
00:17:39,625 --> 00:17:41,500
[KURUMI] We're home.

462
00:17:41,583 --> 00:17:43,375
Whoa. It's so clean here.

463
00:17:43,458 --> 00:17:44,875
Wow, Kuu. You tidied up
while we were gone?

464
00:17:44,958 --> 00:17:45,958
You're welcome.

465
00:17:46,041 --> 00:17:47,833
Thank you. It looks great.

466
00:17:47,916 --> 00:17:49,666
Here, as a reward, have these
chocolates they gave us at--

467
00:17:49,750 --> 00:17:52,416
Aah. Oh, no,
they went everywhere.

468
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:53,875
[sighs]

469
00:17:53,958 --> 00:17:56,083
Uh... where's Kuu?

470
00:17:56,166 --> 00:17:58,041
[water running]

471
00:17:58,125 --> 00:18:00,041
Republic of Palau
Babeldaob Island

472
00:18:00,125 --> 00:18:02,000
Mount Ngerchelchuus

473
00:18:02,083 --> 00:18:04,166
[man singing in Japanese]

474
00:18:07,625 --> 00:18:10,625
♪

475
00:18:12,083 --> 00:18:13,833
[BOY] What? Minako dumped you?

476
00:18:13,916 --> 00:18:15,166
[BOY 2] Hey, keep it down.

477
00:18:15,250 --> 00:18:17,083
--So you're single again?
--Welcome back.

478
00:18:17,166 --> 00:18:19,333
In high school,
love is always on the rocks.

479
00:18:19,416 --> 00:18:22,041
Another reason
I don't get romance.

480
00:18:22,125 --> 00:18:23,916
The whole thing's
a mystery to me.

481
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:26,791
Oh, no. I'm back to staring
at Saiki again.

482
00:18:26,875 --> 00:18:28,541
Chiyo Yumehara.
I don't know why...

483
00:18:28,625 --> 00:18:30,250
but a couple of months ago,

484
00:18:30,333 --> 00:18:32,375
she had a crush on me
and wouldn't leave me alone.

485
00:18:32,458 --> 00:18:34,000
I managed to evade
all her advances,

486
00:18:34,083 --> 00:18:35,833
and eventually,
she gave up on me.

487
00:18:35,916 --> 00:18:37,750
Thought she was going out
with some other guy, but--

488
00:18:37,833 --> 00:18:40,500
He's got such kind eyes,
the cheekbones of a prince,

489
00:18:40,583 --> 00:18:42,333
and fair skin
that just glistens.

490
00:18:42,416 --> 00:18:43,916
I can't take my eyes
off of him.

491
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:46,041
--Get them checked.
--No. Bad Chiyo.

492
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:47,666
You have a boyfriend.

493
00:18:47,750 --> 00:18:50,500
But lately, the thrill is gone.
We've lost our spark.

494
00:18:50,583 --> 00:18:53,500
Those beautiful words that first
made my heart skip a beat.

495
00:18:53,583 --> 00:18:55,541
There's a rain of tears
falling inside your heart.

496
00:18:55,625 --> 00:18:57,791
Please, let me be the umbrella
for your overcast heart.

497
00:18:57,875 --> 00:18:59,958
[overlapping chatter]

498
00:19:00,041 --> 00:19:01,916
[YUMEHARA] Takeru says it
so much, I wanna scream.

499
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:03,958
And when he finally gives that
stupid metaphor a rest

500
00:19:04,041 --> 00:19:05,416
and says something else--

501
00:19:05,500 --> 00:19:06,875
Baby, let me be
the little blue kickboard

502
00:19:06,958 --> 00:19:08,375
for your swimming heart
so it doesn't drown

503
00:19:08,458 --> 00:19:09,750
in the great big ocean
we call life...

504
00:19:09,833 --> 00:19:11,875
It sounds ridiculous.

505
00:19:11,958 --> 00:19:14,083
I see. Breakup season's
come for you, too, huh?

506
00:19:14,166 --> 00:19:15,791
And that's not even
the half of it.

507
00:19:15,875 --> 00:19:18,500
His feet smell horrible.
He chews food as loud as a cow.

508
00:19:18,583 --> 00:19:20,833
The way he holds chopsticks
is totally weird.

509
00:19:20,916 --> 00:19:22,625
He's always a jerk
to store clerks.

510
00:19:22,708 --> 00:19:24,416
He's got the worst
fashion sense.

511
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:26,250
And every time he laughs,
he dislocates his jaw,

512
00:19:26,333 --> 00:19:28,250
which is a total buzz kill.

513
00:19:28,333 --> 00:19:31,708
These days, all I see anymore
are his many, many, many flaws.

514
00:19:31,791 --> 00:19:35,416
Ordinarily, I couldn't care less
about people's relationships.

515
00:19:35,500 --> 00:19:37,083
But considering her history,

516
00:19:37,166 --> 00:19:39,666
she may set her sights on me
again if they break up,

517
00:19:39,750 --> 00:19:41,333
so I have no choice.

518
00:19:41,416 --> 00:19:43,333
I'll be the stand
that protects their umbrella.

519
00:19:43,416 --> 00:19:45,083
So this guy's Takeru?

520
00:19:45,166 --> 00:19:46,083
[laughs then jaw snaps]

521
00:19:46,166 --> 00:19:47,541
[screams]

522
00:19:47,625 --> 00:19:49,083
Are you okay?

523
00:19:49,166 --> 00:19:50,625
[sighs]

524
00:19:50,708 --> 00:19:52,708
Yeah, I'm fine. My jaw
got dislocated. Sorry.

525
00:19:52,791 --> 00:19:54,208
No, we're sorry
for making you laugh.

526
00:19:54,291 --> 00:19:55,750
That really is a buzz kill.

527
00:19:55,833 --> 00:19:57,541
Oh, hey, by the way, Takeru,

528
00:19:57,625 --> 00:19:59,500
how's everything been going
with your girlfriend lately?

529
00:19:59,583 --> 00:20:00,916
--Great.
--Nope, wrong answer.

530
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:02,625
[bell chimes]

531
00:20:02,708 --> 00:20:04,458
Ahh, I feel awful.

532
00:20:04,541 --> 00:20:07,041
Sorry to keep you waiting,
but now that I'm here...

533
00:20:07,125 --> 00:20:08,958
Yeah, it's fine. I just
got here, too. Don't worry.

534
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:10,750
--So, want to do something?
--Whatever.

535
00:20:10,833 --> 00:20:12,291
All right, then let's do
something.

536
00:20:12,375 --> 00:20:13,541
I can't stay out too long.

537
00:20:13,625 --> 00:20:14,791
He thinks this is going great?

538
00:20:14,875 --> 00:20:16,083
Wanna hit the arcade?
Nah.

539
00:20:16,166 --> 00:20:17,875
Is there someplace
you'd rather go?

540
00:20:17,958 --> 00:20:19,708
No, not really.

541
00:20:19,791 --> 00:20:21,666
This relationship's
in worse shape than I thought.

542
00:20:21,750 --> 00:20:25,791
Yumehara's affection for Takeru
is already down to 57.

543
00:20:25,875 --> 00:20:27,750
And it just dropped
three points.

544
00:20:27,833 --> 00:20:31,750
Naturally he forgot that today
is our three-month anniversary.

545
00:20:31,833 --> 00:20:33,958
Ah, girls make a big deal
out of anniversaries.

546
00:20:34,041 --> 00:20:35,416
Even after all these years,

547
00:20:35,500 --> 00:20:37,583
Mom still wants
something special every month.

548
00:20:37,666 --> 00:20:39,041
So did Takeru remember?

549
00:20:39,125 --> 00:20:40,625
I feel so relaxed
when I'm with you.

550
00:20:40,708 --> 00:20:43,250
You're like a massage chair
for my heart.

551
00:20:43,333 --> 00:20:46,666
That's even worse. But I have
no choice, so three months.

552
00:20:46,750 --> 00:20:48,916
--Huh? Three months?
--Wait? What?

553
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:50,916
Wow, you remembered
our three-month anniversary?

554
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:52,416
I'm so touched.

555
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:53,750
[SAIKI] Good.

556
00:20:53,833 --> 00:20:55,583
Yeah, of course,
and I got you something.

557
00:20:55,666 --> 00:20:57,583
--Really? How sweet.
--His likability shot up.

558
00:20:57,666 --> 00:20:59,125
Does he have something for her?

559
00:20:59,208 --> 00:21:00,583
[TAKERU] Crap,
I don't have anything.

560
00:21:00,666 --> 00:21:02,041
--Of course not.
--Score. I've still got...

561
00:21:02,125 --> 00:21:03,625
some of that squid jerky
I was eating in class.

562
00:21:03,708 --> 00:21:05,541
[SAIKI] What girl
wants squid jerky?

563
00:21:05,625 --> 00:21:07,375
--Can I look now?
--I'm ready.

564
00:21:07,458 --> 00:21:09,041
No, you're not.

565
00:21:09,125 --> 00:21:11,166
Oh. How cute. A bunny.

566
00:21:11,250 --> 00:21:13,125
She was eying it
in the window earlier.

567
00:21:13,208 --> 00:21:15,000
Good thing I bought it,
just in case.

568
00:21:15,083 --> 00:21:16,708
Don't worry.
I'll take the money...

569
00:21:16,791 --> 00:21:19,250
out of your wallet later
to reimburse myself.

570
00:21:19,333 --> 00:21:20,666
I smelled squid jerky,
and for a second,

571
00:21:20,750 --> 00:21:22,291
I was afraid
that was gonna be my gift.

572
00:21:22,375 --> 00:21:23,750
Like, I would do that.

573
00:21:23,833 --> 00:21:26,125
[NARRATOR] Saiki
continued to help Takeru out,

574
00:21:26,208 --> 00:21:28,166
trying to boost
his likability score for Chiyo.

575
00:21:28,250 --> 00:21:30,750
And finally, it hit 90,
a major milestone.

576
00:21:30,833 --> 00:21:32,375
[YUMEHARA]
I'm having the best time today.

577
00:21:32,458 --> 00:21:34,791
--Right? Let's grab dinner.
--Sounds good.

578
00:21:34,875 --> 00:21:36,750
--The burgers there are--
--Okonomiyaki.

579
00:21:36,833 --> 00:21:38,666
--Okonomiyaki.
--No way.

580
00:21:38,750 --> 00:21:41,625
You must've read my mind. I was
thinking about Okonomiyaki.

581
00:21:41,708 --> 00:21:43,791
His score's so high,

582
00:21:43,875 --> 00:21:45,416
I wouldn't be surprised
if she married him.

583
00:21:45,500 --> 00:21:47,958
There's no way
they're gonna break up now.

584
00:21:48,041 --> 00:21:50,041
[MAN] Welcome. Party of two?

585
00:21:50,125 --> 00:21:52,250
Oh, wow, you can count. Now
take us to our table, dumbass.

586
00:21:54,166 --> 00:21:58,208
Man, I'm starving.
This is great.

587
00:21:58,291 --> 00:22:00,208
[talks with mouth full]

588
00:22:00,291 --> 00:22:02,625
Uch...

589
00:22:02,708 --> 00:22:04,875
I can't take it anymore.
Goodbye.

590
00:22:04,958 --> 00:22:06,541
Huh? Hey, wait.

591
00:22:06,625 --> 00:22:08,416
Oh, right.

592
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:11,958
Likability can plummet
in an instant, too. Ahh.

593
00:22:12,041 --> 00:22:14,833
♪

594
00:22:21,666 --> 00:22:24,541
[woman singing ending theme
in Japanese]

595
00:23:42,666 --> 00:23:43,833
[SAIKI]
Sports Day.

596
00:23:43,916 --> 00:23:45,875
My least-favorite school
event is approaching.

597
00:23:45,958 --> 00:23:48,833
And as Hairo said,
a month will pass in no time.

598
00:23:48,916 --> 00:23:51,416
Next time on <i>The Disastrous</i>
<i>Life of Saiki K.,</i>

599
00:23:51,500 --> 00:23:53,041
I'll live every day
to the fullest

600
00:23:53,125 --> 00:23:56,250
by being extremely cautious
and never letting my guard down.

